com.foreach.across.modules.entity.bind

Interface EntityPropertyValues

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EntityPropertiesBinder

    public interface EntityPropertyValues
    Facade for accessing individual properties of an EntityPropertyRegistry for a specific entity instance. All properties are required to have a valid EntityPropertyDescriptor that is used to determine how the property should be handled.

    An EntityPropertyValues represents a detached instance of the properties. Values can be set for a property, but that does not mean it is immediately applied ("flushed") to the target entity. When and how the latter happens is implementation dependent.

    Since:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    EntityPropertiesBinder, EntityPropertyBinder
